nodeName - Simplest way to choose a node

Ex: 
spec:
  nodeName: minikube-m02
nodeSelector - To choose nodes by node label
Ex: 
spec:
  nodeSelector:
    team: Java
 
affinity - For advanced options like Exists, Gt, Lt, In, etc..

  nodeAffinity - To choose nodes

   Types of Node Affinity:
   1) requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
   
   ex:
   spec:
     nodeAffinity:
       requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
         nodeSelectorTerms:
           - matchExpressions:
               - key: rank
                 operator: Lt
                 values:
                   - "5"

   2) prefferedDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:

   ex:
   spec:
     nodeAffinity:
       preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
         - weight: 40 
           preference:
             matchExpressions:
               key: "team"
               operator: In
               values: ["analytics"]
         - weight: 60
           preference:
             matchExpressions:
               key: rank
               operator: Lt
               values:
                 - "5"

  podAffinity - To co-locate pods with pod labels topology Key
  podAntiAffinity - To keep away pods with pod labels topologyKey

  ex: 
   spec:
     podAffinity:
       requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
         - labelSelector:
             matchExpressions:
               - key: app
                 operator: In
                 values:
                   - "todo-ui"
           topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname

Taint - Added onto node. Only pods which can tolerate this taint can be scheduled
  NoSchedule - Hard (Do not schedule pods if they can't tolerate)
  PreferNoSchedule - Soft (Can be scheduled if no other nodes available)
  NoExecute - Strict (Delete running pods also if they can't tolerate newly added taint)
